cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC 

This paper deals with a dataset that contains transcribed DVS, which is temporally aligned to full length HD movies. The paper proposes different approaches for generating video descriptions and compares DVS to scripts. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper also uses machine learning techniques to generate video descriptions, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with accessibility for visually impaired people, which makes cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) a possible sub-category.
